  "prompt": "International awards of Shahrukh Khan?",
  "response": "Shah Rukh Khan, the celebrated Indian actor and film producer, has received numerous awards and honors throughout his career, both nationally and internationally. Some notable international awards and recognitions include:\n\n1. **Ordre des Arts et des Lettres** (2007) - Khan was awarded this prestigious French honor for his contributions to the arts.\n\n2. **World Economic Forum's Crystal Award** (2018) - This award recognizes outstanding contributions by individuals to society and Khan was honored for his leadership in social causes.\n\n3. **UNESCO Pyramide con Marni** (2011) - Shah Rukh Khan received this award for his charitable work and efforts to support children's education.\n\n4. **Malaysia's Cinema Legend Award** (2012) - This award was received during the Malaysia International Film Festival.\n\n5. **Asian Award for Outstanding Contribution to Cinema** (2017) - This is a significant honor in the Asian community recognizing Khan's influence and contributions to cinema.\n\n6. **Golden and Platinum Jubilee Awards** - Received from various film festivals and organizations worldwide for his cinematic contributions.\n\n7. **Honorary Doctorate from the University of Edinburgh** (2015) - Recognized for his philanthropic efforts and contributions to the film industry.\n\n8. **Star of the Year \u2013 Male** at the ZEE Cine Awards (International) - Recognized multiple times for his performances.\n\nThese awards reflect not only his talent as an actor but also his influence as a cultural icon and philanthropist. Additionally, he's recognized as one of the richest actors in the world and has a massive fan following across the globe.",
